Row with max 1s



You are given a 2D binary array arr[][] consisting of only 
1s and 0s. Each row of the array is sorted in non-decreasing 
order. Your task is to find and return the index of the first 
row that contains the maximum number of 1s. If no such row exists, return -1.







class Solution {
  public:
    int rowWithMax1s(vector<vector<int>> &arr) {
        // code here
        int maxi=INT_MIN;
        int count;
        int p=-1;
        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            count=0;
            for(int j=0;j<arr[0].size();j++){
                if(arr[i][j]==1){
                    count++;
                }
            }
            if(maxi<count){
                maxi=count;
                p=i;
            }
        }
        return p;
    }
};
